Reasoning: The paper deals with the co-deployment of RF and VLC technologies in indoor environments to enhance network performances and address specific QoS constraints. This falls under the domain of networked systems and communication technologies, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as it covers research on network architectures, protocols, and applications. The paper also deals with information theory and communication technologies, which are covered by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking). The paper also involves system-level analysis and optimization, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
